title: Firefox suddenly slow and unresponsive after recent update (Windows 10)
content:
Hi everyone,

Since the latest Firefox update (just installed automatically), my browser has become very slow and often unresponsive — especially when opening new tabs or loading pages with multiple images/videos. I’ve tried restarting Firefox and my PC, but it hasn’t helped.

Details:

Firefox version: latest (updated yesterday)

Operating System: Windows 10

Issue started right after update

Pages take 10–20+ seconds to load

Sometimes “Not Responding” appears

Hardware acceleration is currently enabled

Extensions I use: uBlock Origin, Bitwarden, Dark Reader

Troubleshooting steps I’ve already tried:

Disabled extensions → no improvement

Cleared cache and cookies

Restarted Firefox and PC

Checked for Windows updates

Questions:

Is this a known issue with the recent Firefox update?

Are there recommended settings (e.g., disabling hardware acceleration) to improve performance?

Should I roll back to an earlier Firefox version temporarily?

Any other steps I should try to fix this?

Thanks in advance for your help! Premium Scrubs
